The paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks for image recognition and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of supervised learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with ultrasound images, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the estimation of complex multidirectional flow, which could fall under the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category.
